# Backend rules

The repo is currently a static portfolio; backend work starts with the contact
endpoint (TD-004).

- Use Next route handlers (`src/app/api/<name>/route.ts`).
- **Validate all input server-side** (e.g. zod); never trust the client.
- Secrets via env vars only; never logged or committed.
- Return structured, safe errors (no stack traces to clients).
- Rate-limit public/mutating endpoints.
- Parameterized DB access; least-privilege auth (JWT/OAuth + RBAC) when added.
- Add tests for happy and failure paths.
- Record notable decisions as ADRs (`.ai/decisions`).
